DESCRIPTION:Philippe Croizon\, a 26-year-old metal worker at Fonderies du 
 Poitou\, had no idea that his life would be turned upside down on March 5\
 , 1994. On that day\, the young father received three 20\,000 V shocks whi
 le trying to dismantle the TV antenna hanging from the chimney of his hous
 e in Saint-Rémy-sur-Creuse. After two months in a coma\, he woke up with 
